he core problem with journalism today. At its heart, Min maintains, traditional shoe-leather reporting—knocking on doors, talking to people, careful observation and analysis—is still the best way for journalism to serve its civic purpose. Thoughtful and engaging, Rethinking the New Technology of Journalism is a compelling call for news gathering to return to its roots. Reporters, those studying and teaching journalism, and avid consumers of the media will be interested in this book.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Journalism.2bisacsh  aInternet.  aJournalism.  aartificial intelligence.  ablockchain.  adata journalism.  adigital media.  afield theory.  ajournalism innovation.  ajournalistic profession.  anewsroom computerization.  aprinting press.  aslow journalism.  aslow media.  asocial construction of technology.  asocial media.  atechnological determinism.  atechnology.  atelegraph.  avirtual reality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Library and Information Science 2022 Englishz978311099318908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Library and Information Science 2022z9783110993103oZDB-23-DGB08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107669290 cprintz978027109248540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978027109262140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271092621423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271092621/original  a978-3-11-076692-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3